                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4731/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sydney</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-08T15:00:00+10:00"
                            >March 8, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 9—6:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In interview with the Minister for Customs requested by him today he referred to
                    negotiations in progress for commercial treaties with several governments and
                    stated that Australian Government would like to negotiate commercial treaty with
                    the United States. He will send me information regarding nature of the
                    Australian proposals.</p>
                <p>I had not been able previously to take up exchange of notes referred to in the
                    Department’s instruction of January 30th and under the circumstances it seemed
                    unwise to mention it to him today. I will postpone action regarding notes until
                    further instructed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
